Your shock patient has about 45 minutes until their kidneys begin to die, at which point they'll be useful only for organ donation as the heart will have died 44 minutes prior.
replyContent: Riaz, You misunderstood what that single question is asking, the kidneys begin to suffer before the heart does IN THE STATE OF SHOCK. Not after the pt. has died. This is how pts suffering from shock for long periods eventually die: kidney failure. You mention "massive" amounts of mistakes. Please Email us with any further misunderstandings.
